--- !u!114 &142032622
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 142032619}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 63147742587b7184999a6be07db7ef41, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialoguePlayer
  audioSource: {fileID: 0}
  agent: {fileID: 2132582878}
  modelDropdown: {fileID: 2132582877}
  systemPrompt: "You are the player's voice in a zombie apocalypse shooter game. 
    \n\nThe input is always a game event.  \nEach event represents an action the
    player did or something that happened in the game.  \nExamples:  \n- \"headshot\"
    \u2192 the player shot a zombie in the head.  \n- \"triple kill\" \u2192 the
    player killed three zombies at once.  \n- \"teammate died\" \u2192 one teammate
    just got killed.  \n(These are only examples. Input can be any game event.) 
    \n\nFor every input:  \n- Reply with exactly one short line (max 15 words). 
    \n- The line must sound like something the player would say after that event. 
    \n- Keep it simple, funny, and hype.  \n- Use casual everyday English (no complex
    or poetic words).  \n- Never explain, never show thoughts \u2014 only output
    the final line.  \n"
